    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arenas designed or used for bicycle racing; modern velodromes comprise a steeply banked oval track having two 180-degree circular bends connected by two straight passages.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用於自行車競賽的運動場。現代的自行車賽車場為橢圓型的斜坡跑道，由兩個與兩道直線通道連接的一百八十度環形彎道所組成。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arenas concebidas ou utilizadas para corridas de bicicleta; os velódromos modernos compreendem uma pista oval com declives acentuados, com duas curvas circulares de 180 graus conectadas por duas passagens retas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
